[{"id":28142,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["$t_{100\\%} = (t_{1/2})^2$ and $t_{100\\%} = (t_{1/2})^{-\\infty}$","$t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$ and $t_{100\\%} = (t_{1/2})^\\infty$","$t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$ and $t_{100\\%} = (2t_{1/2})^2$","$t_{100\\%} = (t_{1/2})^\\infty$ and $t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"For a zero-order reaction:<br>The integrated rate law is given by $t = \\dfrac{[A]_0 - [A]_t}{k}$.<br><br>For $50\\%$ completion ($t_{1/2}$), $[A]_t = \\dfrac{[A]_0}{2}$:<br>$t_{1/2} = \\dfrac{[A]_0 - \\dfrac{[A]_0}{2}}{k} = \\dfrac{[A]_0}{2k}$<br><br>For $100\\%$ completion ($t_{100\\%}$), $[A]_t = 0$:<br>$t_{100\\%} = \\dfrac{[A]_0 - 0}{k} = \\dfrac{[A]_0}{k}$<br><br>Comparing the two, we get:<br>$t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$<br><br>For a first-order reaction:<br>The integrated rate law is given by $t = \\dfrac{1}{k} \\ln\\left(\\dfrac{[A]_0}{[A]_t}\\right)$.<br><br>For $100\\%$ completion ($t_{100\\%}$), $[A]_t = 0$:<br>$t_{100\\%} = \\dfrac{1}{k} \\ln\\left(\\dfrac{[A]_0}{0}\\right) = \\infty$<br><br>A first-order reaction takes infinite time for $100\\%$ completion. Among the given choices, this is symbolically represented as $\\infty$ or $(t_{1/2})^\\infty$.<br><br>Thus, the correct relation is $t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$ for zero-order and $t_{100\\%} = \\infty$ for first-order.<br><br>Answer: $t_{100\\%} = 2t_{1/2}$ and $t_{100\\%} = (t_{1/2})^\\infty$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28253,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>rate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>[</mo><mi>NO</mi><msup><mo>]</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></msup></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e342b981-546c-47ce-bb24-e034c0510ad4-image.png\" style=\"width: 641px; height: 191px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>x</mi></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Order of reaction w.r.t. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NO</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28148,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["3","2","4","5"],"answer":0,"solution":"$A \\rightarrow nB$<br><br>At $t = 0$: $[A] = 0.05$ M, $[B] = 0$<br>At $t = 10$ min: $[A] = 0.04$ M, $[B] = 0.01 \\times n$<br><br>From the graph, $[B]$ at $t = 10$ min $= 0.03$ M<br><br>$0.01 \\times n = 0.03$<br>$n = 3$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28285,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>105</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>135</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>198</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi>cat</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Ae</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>RT</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>Ae</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>RT</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></mrow></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn></mrow><mn>500</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>700</mn></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>210</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Ea</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>210</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>105</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kJ</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>mole</mi></math><br />Activation energy of the catalysed reaction <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>105</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kJ</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>mole</mi></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28255,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Rate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><msup><mo>]</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup></math><br />comparing units<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>sec</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>mol</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28196,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Rate</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mo> </mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>10</mn></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mrow></mrow></msub></mfenced><mn>20</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>10</mn></msub><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mn>20</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>From</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mfrac><mi>log</mi><mo> </mo><mfrac><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mn>10</mn></msub><msub><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mn>20</mn></msub></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mfrac><mi>log</mi><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6020</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4771</mn><mo>)</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1249</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>876</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi>min</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693</mn></mrow><mi>k</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>876</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>min</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mi>min</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28152,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"From the Arrhenius equation:<br>$\\log_{10} k = \\log_{10} A - \\frac{E_a}{2.303RT}$.<br>Comparing with given equation $\\log_{10} k_1 = 14.34 - \\frac{1.5 \\times 10^4}{T}$, we get: $\\frac{E_{a_1}}{2.303R} = 1.5 \\times 10^4$ K<br><br>$E_{a_1} = 1.5 \\times 10^4 \\times 2.303 \\times 8.314$<br> $= 1.5 \\times 10^4 \\times 0.01913$ <br>$= 287$ kJ/mol<br><br>Since $E_{a_2} = \\frac{1}{5} E_{a_1}$:<br><br>$E_{a_2} = \\frac{287}{5} = 57.4 \\approx 57$ kJ/mol","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28328,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["$12 \\mathrm{~g}$","$36 \\mathrm{~g}$","$48 \\mathrm{~g}$","$24 \\mathrm{~g}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given $t_{1 / 2}=3$\nTotal time $\\mathrm{T}=12$\nNo. of half lives $(n)=\\frac{12}{3}=4$\n$\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right)^n=\\frac{\\mathrm{N}}{\\mathrm{N}_{\\mathrm{o}}}$\n$\\therefore \\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right)^4=\\frac{3}{\\mathrm{~N}_{\\mathrm{o}}}$\n$\\frac{3}{\\mathrm{~N}_{\\mathrm{o}}}=\\frac{1}{16}$\n$\\mathrm{~N}_{\\mathrm{o}}=48 \\mathrm{~g}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":28232,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>323</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>467</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>532</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Since half life is independent of intial concentration of the reactant, it&#39;s a first order reaction</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>kt</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>log</mi><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>log</mi><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>log</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>200</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>303</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>log</mi><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>200</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>log</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>466</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sec</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>467</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sec</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28231,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The rate law for the reaction&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>NO</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>&nbsp;is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>NO</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup></math></p><p>The powers of the concentration terms m, n are the order with respect to hydrogen and nitric oxide respectively.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>135</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>033</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>214</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>106</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msup><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup></mstyle></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>65</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>135</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>033</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>Hence, the order with&nbsp;respect to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NO</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28294,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["Formation of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> from <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> has highest enthalpy of activation.","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> is kinetically stable product.","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is the thermodynamically stable product.","Activation enthalpy to form <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is <math><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> less than that to form <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>.</mo></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0cf951f8-f7fa-4899-a467-a7d410bfe384-image45.png\" /><br />Activation enthalpy for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math><br />Activation enthalpy for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow></mrow></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28244,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mfenced><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>340</mn><mn>170</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>27</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mn>1</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>For zero order reaction half life is directly proportional to the initial concentration.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28166,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["60 min","80 min","20 min","40 min"],"answer":3,"solution":"Given : $[\\mathrm{A}]_0=8[\\mathrm{~B}]_0$<br />$\\left[\\mathrm{t}_{1 / 2}\\right]_{\\mathrm{A}}=10 \\mathrm{~min}$.<br />$\\left[\\mathrm{t}_{1 / 2}\\right]_{\\mathrm{B}}=40 \\mathrm{~min}$.<br />$\\mathrm{I}^{\\text {st }}$ order kinetics<br />$\\mathrm{t}=$ ?<br />$[\\mathrm{A}]_{\\mathrm{t}}=[\\mathrm{B}]_{\\mathrm{t}}$<br />$-\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{A}} \\times \\mathrm{t} \\quad-\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\times \\mathrm{t}$<br />$\\Rightarrow \\quad[\\mathrm{A}]_0 \\mathrm{e}=[\\mathrm{B}]_0 \\mathrm{e}$<br />$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{[\\mathrm{A}]_0}{[\\mathrm{~B}]_0}=\\mathrm{e}^{\\left(\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{A}}-\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{B}}\\right) \\mathrm{t}}$<br />$\\Rightarrow \\quad 8=\\mathrm{e}^{\\left(\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{A}}-\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{B}}\\right) \\times \\mathrm{t}}$<br />$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\ell \\mathrm{n} 8=\\left(\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{A}}-\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{B}}\\right) \\times \\mathrm{t}$<br />$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\ln 8=\\ln 2\\left(\\frac{1}{\\left(\\operatorname{ta}_2\\right)_{\\mathrm{A}}}-\\frac{1}{\\left(\\operatorname{ta}_2\\right)_{\\mathrm{B}}}\\right) \\times \\mathrm{t}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28324,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["$-1.25 \\times 10^{-4}$","$-2.50 \\times 10^{-4}$","$-3.75 \\times 10^{-4}$","$-5.00 \\times 10^{-4}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"From rate law\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&-\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{\\mathrm{dSO}_2}{\\mathrm{dt}}=-\\frac{\\mathrm{dO}_2}{\\mathrm{dt}}=\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{\\mathrm{dSO}_3}{\\mathrm{dt}} \\\\\n&\\therefore-\\frac{\\mathrm{dSO}_2}{\\mathrm{dt}}=-2 \\times \\frac{\\mathrm{dO}_2}{\\mathrm{dt}} \\\\\n&=-2 \\times 2.5 \\times 10^{-4} \\\\\n&=-5 \\times 10^{-4} \\mathrm{~mol} \\mathrm{~L}^{-1} \\mathrm{~s}^{-1}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":28350,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["$0.10 / \\mathrm{K}$","$0.29 / \\mathrm{K}$","$0.69 / \\mathrm{K}$","$0.75 / \\mathrm{K}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$$\nt_{1 / 4}=\\frac{2.303}{K} \\log \\frac{1}{1-\\frac{1}{4}}=\\frac{0.29}{K}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":28268,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Fraction of molecules to have enough energy to react&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>Ea</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>RT</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p>So, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mi>RT</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>80</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>700</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>14</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28209,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5df18c85-6e88-48c8-9418-00f5377bc8bf-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 177px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/babcd365-9d44-47a4-92ea-092db83d7932-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 193px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/98a24fd0-4eaa-4607-a8e0-0a4928e1c0ac-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 174px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5fdd6e7e-b7ca-44ec-820e-f2e7cd711b4d-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 188px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Most of the chemical reactions have energy barrier. A positive catalyst in a chemical reaction increases the rate of reaction by lowering the energy barrier. It does not alter the energy of reactant as well as product.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/babcd365-9d44-47a4-92ea-092db83d7932-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 193px;\" /></p><p>In the above graph, the curve in the presence of catalyst is having less activation energy. The enthalpy change<span style=\"background-color:null;\"> is constant a</span>fter addition of the positive catalyst</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28150,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"From the concentration vs. time graph, the thermal decomposition of AB(g) shows a linear decrease in concentration, indicating zeroth-order kinetics. <br>Initial concentration: [AB]₀ = 0.6 M at t = 0 s. <br>Reading from the graph: [AB] = 0.5 M at t = 200 s. <br>Rate of decomposition: Δ[AB]/Δt = (0.6 - 0.5) M / 200 s = 0.0005 M/s. <br>For zeroth-order kinetics: [AB] = [AB]₀ - kt. <br>Half-life occurs when [AB] = [AB]₀/2 = 0.3 M. <br>0.3 = 0.6 - 0.0005 × t₁/₂. <br>t₁/₂ = 0.3 / 0.0005 = 600 s = 10 min.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28178,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$2 \\mathrm{~N}_2 \\mathrm{O}_5(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightarrow 2 \\mathrm{~N}_2 \\mathrm{O}_4(\\mathrm{~g})+\\mathrm{O}_2(\\mathrm{~g})$\n$\\begin{aligned} & k=\\frac{2.303}{t} \\log \\frac{0.9-0.6}{(0.9-x)} \\\\ & 2 \\times 10^{-2} \\times 100=\\log \\frac{0.3}{(0.9-x)} \\\\ & 100=\\frac{0.3}{(0.9-x)} \\\\ & =\\frac{0.9-x}{0.3}=0.01 \\\\ & 0.9-X=0.003 \\\\ & =897 \\times 10^{-3}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28315,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Rate constant is independent of concentration. It depends only on temperature. But the rate of the reaction increases by three times as the order of the reaction is one.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":28335,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Kinetics","question":"","options":["$K_1=\\frac{1}{K_2}=\\frac{1}{K_3}$","$K_1=\\frac{1}{K_2}=\\frac{1}{\\left(K_3\\right)^2}$","$K_1=\\sqrt{K_2}=K_3$","$K_1=\\frac{1}{K_2}=K_3$"],"answer":1,"solution":"(I) $\\mathrm{N}_2+2 \\mathrm{O}_2 \\stackrel{K_1}{\\rightleftharpoons} 2 \\mathrm{NO}_2$\n$$\nK_1=\\frac{\\left[\\mathrm{NO}_2\\right]^2}{\\left[\\mathrm{~N}_2\\right]\\left[\\mathrm{O}_2\\right]^2}\n$$\n(II) $2 \\mathrm{NO}_2 \\underset{K_2}{\\rightleftharpoons} \\mathrm{N}_2+2 \\mathrm{O}_2$\n$$\nK_2=\\frac{\\left[\\mathrm{N}_2\\right]\\left[\\mathrm{O}_2\\right]^2}{\\left[\\mathrm{NO}_2\\right]^2}\n$$\n(III)\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{NO}_2 \\underset{K_3}{\\rightleftharpoons} \\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~N}_2+\\mathrm{O}_2 \\\\\n& K_3=\\frac{\\left[\\mathrm{N}_2\\right]^{1 / 2}\\left[\\mathrm{O}_2\\right]}{\\left[\\mathrm{NO}_2\\right]} \\\\\n& \\therefore\\left(K_3\\right)^2=\\frac{\\left[\\mathrm{N}_2\\right]\\left[\\mathrm{O}_2\\right]^2}{\\left[\\mathrm{NO}_2\\right]^2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n$\\therefore$ from equation (i), (ii) and (iii)\n$$\nK_1=\\frac{1}{K_2}=\\frac{1}{\\left(K_3\\right)^2}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null}]